      <exercise id="fs-id1169738163099" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1169738163102">    <para id="import-auto-id1320322">
      <title>Integrated Concepts</title>
    </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id2875753">Suppose we replace the 4.0-kg book in <link target-id="fs-id1169737911368"/> of the biceps muscle with an elastic exercise rope that obeys Hooke’s Law. Assume its force constant <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>k</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mtext>600</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>N/m</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{k="600"`"N/m"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. (a) How much is the rope stretched (past equilibrium) to provide the same force <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>F</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>B</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{F rSub { size 8{B} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> as in this example? Assume the rope is held in the hand at the same location as the book. (b) What force is on the biceps muscle if the exercise rope is pulled straight up so that the forearm makes an angle of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>25º</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"25"°} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> with the horizontal? Assume the biceps muscle is still perpendicular to the forearm.</para></problem></exercise>

      <exercise id="fs-id1169738110743" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1169738110747">
